  <!-- Marketing -->
  <div style="background:#D6ECFA; border-radius:20px; padding:2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <h3 style="color:#1a325d; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700;">Marketing – Use Your Dependability to Build Trust at Scale</h3>
    <p>
      You’re reliable and trusted by your clients, but now it’s time to show the world what you’re capable of. You don’t need to be flashy — you just need to share your value consistently so others can see it.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Moves to execute:</strong> Client Success Stories: Your clients already trust you. Turn that trust into marketing. Create case studies, testimonials, and videos that highlight the success you’ve brought them.
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>What to do:</em> Ask for testimonials after every successful project. Create videos or write blog posts where your clients share their success stories. Share these consistently on your website and social media.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div style="background:#D6ECFA; border-radius:20px; padding:2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <h3 style="color:#1a325d; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700;">Simple - Relatable Content Creation:</h3>
    <p>
      You don’t need to be an expert in content creation. Just share your stories and how you help clients. Your audience connects with you because they trust you.
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>What to do:</em> Start posting regularly about your work: client success, behind-the-scenes insights, and why you do what you do. Use simple language and make it relatable.

<p>
      <strong>Result:</strong> You transform your reputation into a repeatable growth system that steadily attracts new clients.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Referrals -->
  <div style="background:#D6ECFA; border-radius:20px; padding:2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <h3 style="color:#1a325d; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700;">Referral Program:</h3>
    <p>
      You already get referrals naturally — now, let’s formalize that with a referral system.
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>What to do:</em> Create a referral program where you reward clients who send new business your way. Track it with a Google Sheet or CRM, and reward clients with a thank-you gift, discount, or bonus.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Result:</strong> You turn your trustworthiness into a scalable marketing engine that consistently brings in new clients.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Sales -->
  <div style="background:#D6ECFA; border-radius:20px; padding:2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <h3 style="color:#1a325d; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700;">Sheep Sales System:</h3>
    <p>
      Leverage Your Relational Skills into a Repeatable Sales Process
You’re great at connecting and building relationships, but you need a system to ensure those relationships turn into consistent sales.
    </p>
    <p>
<strong>Moves to execute:</strong>
Sales Script - Create a sales script that highlights your ability to connect with people, but also moves them through the process to close.</p>
      <p> 
<em>What to do:</em> Write a sales script that includes relationship-building steps like asking discovery questions to uncover pain points, and moving the conversation into closing once trust is established.</p>
      <p>Automate Follow-Ups: You’re great at follow-ups, but automate them to stay consistent without doing it all manually.</p>
      <p>
<em>What to do:</em> Set up automated follow-up sequences (emails, texts) for your leads, and schedule reminders for you or your team to follow up at key points in the sales process.</p>
      <p>
<strong>Result:</strong> You turn your relational skills into a repeatable, scalable sales process that can be executed without you.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Leadership -->
  <div style="background:#D6ECFA; border-radius:20px; padding:2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <h3 style="color:#1a325d; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700;">Sheep Leadership Team:</h3>
    <p>
      Lead With Support and Structure
You are naturally a supportive leader, but to scale, you need to lead with confidence and delegate to give your team ownership.</p>
    <p>
<strong>Moves to execute:</strong> Clear KPIs - Set measurable KPIs for your team based on client satisfaction, referrals, and sales performance</p>
    <p>
<em>What to do:</em> Define SMART goals (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound) for each team member. Post them publicly and track them regularly.</p>
    <p>Delegate Leadership: You’re great at supporting others, but now it’s time to give others more responsibility and trust them with leadership.</p>
    <p>
    <em>What to do:</em> Pick 2 team members to mentor and start delegating leadership roles. Give them responsibility for client calls or managing smaller projects.</p>
    <p>1:1 Meetings: Hold weekly check-ins with your team to discuss both their performance and personal goals.</p>
     <p>
<em>What to do:</em> Schedule weekly 1:1s to discuss KPIs and also focus on personal development. This shows you care about their growth, which builds loyalty and engagement.</p>
    <p>
<strong>Result:</strong> You empower your team to take ownership and lead independently, allowing you to focus on high-level growth.</p>

</div>

